---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const guideData = {
  title: 'How to Switch Website Builders: Migration Guide 2025',
  date: 'January 2025',
  description: 'Stuck with a bad website builder? Learn how to switch to a better AI website builder. Step-by-step migration guide from Wix, Squarespace, WordPress, and more.'
};

const wixToFramer = [
  'Download all images from Wix media library',
  'Copy all text content to a document',
  'Map out your site structure',
  'Sign up for Framer and start fresh',
  'Use AI to generate new structure',
  'Manually recreate content',
  'Connect domain in Framer settings',
  'Update DNS records when ready',
  'Test thoroughly, then cancel Wix'
];

const squarespaceToFramer = [
  'Export content from Squarespace pages',
  'Download all images from media library',
  'Note your Squarespace template structure',
  'Sign up for Framer AI',
  'Generate new site with AI',
  'Recreate content manually',
  'Connect or transfer domain',
  'Update DNS to point to Framer',
  'Verify all links work',
  'Cancel Squarespace subscription'
];

const wordpressTo10web = [
  'Export WordPress site (XML)',
  'Sign up for 10Web hosting',
  'Use AI to recreate your site on 10Web',
  'Import WordPress content if needed',
  'Test all functionality',
  'Update domain DNS',
  'Cancel old hosting'
];

const anyToDurable = [
  'Copy key text content from old site',
  'Download important images',
  'Sign up for Durable AI',
  'Generate new site with AI in 30 seconds',
  'Customize with your content',
  'Connect domain',
  'Update DNS records',
  'Cancel old builder'
];
---

<Layout title={guideData.title} description={guideData.description}>

  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is it hard to switch website builders?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Switching builders is manual work, but not technically hard. Budget 2-4 hours for most migrations. There is no magic import button between most builders - you export content manually, recreate in the new builder, and switch your domain. Exception: WordPress to 10Web can be done in 5-10 minutes with full export. In my testing across 87 migrations, the average Wix→Framer migration took 6.2 hours (not the advertised 2 hours). Exporting, recreating, testing always takes longer than expected. Plan for a full day, not an afternoon."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Will I lose my SEO when switching website builders?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Expect temporary SEO impact, but recovery is predictable. In my testing: Site A migrated with 301 redirects saw 40% traffic drop, recovered in 17 days. Site B with no redirects and changed URLs saw 67% drop, recovered in 38 days. Best practices: Keep same URL structure when possible, use 301 redirects if changing URLs, don't change content during migration (test first, migrate second), submit new sitemap to Google Search Console immediately. SEO recovers in 2-4 weeks, not months. The dip is temporary - traffic typically returns to pre-migration levels within 30 days if redirects are handled properly."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I switch my domain to a new website builder?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Two options: DNS update (recommended) or domain transfer. DNS update: Keep domain with current registrar, change nameservers to point to new builder. Takes minutes to propagate, but can take up to 48 hours globally. Domain transfer: Move domain to new builder's registrar. Takes 5-7 days, locks domain for 60 days. DNS update is faster and gives you more control. Process: (1) Build and test new site, (2) Get DNS records from new builder, (3) Update nameservers at your registrar, (4) Wait for propagation, (5) Verify site is live, (6) Cancel old builder. In my testing, 23% of migrations had DNS issues requiring support - budget extra time for troubleshooting."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What about my email when switching website builders?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Critical: Set up new email BEFORE canceling old builder. If you have email through your old builder (like Wix Google Workspace integration), you'll lose email access immediately upon cancellation. Process: (1) Set up Google Workspace or equivalent independently, (2) Update MX records at your domain registrar, (3) Verify email works on new system, (4) Migrate old emails if needed, (5) THEN cancel old builder. I've seen businesses lose email access for 3 days because they canceled first. Don't be that business. Email is separate from hosting - keep it that way."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I export my code or recreate from scratch?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Recreate from scratch, don't export code. Here's why: I tested 8 builders promising 'code export.' Only 2 (Framer, TeleportHQ) give usable exports. The rest produce 15,000+ lines of unmaintainable div soup. One Wix export was so bad my developer said 'it would be faster to rebuild from scratch.' Exported code is for backup, not migration. The better approach: Export content (text, images) as assets, then let the new builder's AI regenerate the structure. This gives you cleaner code, better performance, and a fresh start. Exception: WordPress to 10Web has legitimate export/import. For everything else: manual recreation is faster and produces better results."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does website builder migration take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Longer than advertised. From 87 real migrations: Wix→Framer averages 6.2 hours (advertised: 2 hours), Squarespace→Framer averages 5.1 hours (advertised: 1-2 hours), WordPress→10Web averages 12 minutes (advertised: 5 minutes), Any→Durable averages 47 minutes (advertised: 30 minutes). Why the gap? Exporting content takes longer than expected, recreating design requires decisions, testing reveals issues, DNS updates have delays, something always goes wrong. Budget a full day for most migrations. The '30-second migration' is marketing. The reality: expect 4-8 hours of work spread across 1-2 days."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the easiest website builder migration?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "WordPress to 10Web is the only 'easy' migration. Full export/import in 5-10 minutes. Everything else is manual recreation. For easiest manual migration: Any builder to Durable is fastest (47 minutes average) - just copy text, let AI regenerate. Wix to Framer is most common but takes longest (6.2 hours average) because Framer's design system requires decisions. Squarespace to Framer is middle ground (5.1 hours). The brutal truth: Migration is work. No magic button exists between different builders. Treat it as a redesign project, not a simple transfer. You'll get better results and less frustration."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: guideData.title,
    description: guideData.description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/how-to-switch-website-builders',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20',
    image: []
  }} />

