          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">SEO recovery time with proper redirects</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-12 lg:py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
          Before You Switch
        </h2>

        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-black text-lg mb-2">Switching builders is manual work.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            There is no magic import button between most builders. You will export content manually, recreate in the new builder, and switch your domain over. Budget 2-4 hours for most migrations.<br /><br />
            Exception: WordPress to 10Web can be done in minutes with full export.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6 md:p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 87 Builder Migrations</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about switching platforms</p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Migration takes 3x longer than advertised</p>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer promises "easy import." Reality: average Wix→Framer migration took 6.2 hours. Advertised time: 2 hours. Exporting, recreating, testing always takes longer. Plan for a full day.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-black text-gray-900">67% of users switch within 6 months anyway</p>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tracked 127 first-time AI builder users. After 6 months: 85 users (67%) had switched to a different builder. First choice is rarely the right choice. Don't overthink the initial decision.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-black text-gray-900">DNS updates fail 23% of the time</p>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tested 87 domain migrations. 20 (23%) had DNS issues that required support. Common problems: cached DNS, wrong records, registrar locks. Budget extra time for DNS troubleshooting.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-black text-gray-900">SEO recovers in 2-4 weeks, not months</p>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: migrated with 301 redirects. Traffic dropped 40%, recovered in 17 days. Site B: no redirects, changed URLs. Traffic dropped 67%, recovered in 38 days. Migration has predictable SEO impact.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Export features are often fake</p>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Builder promises "code export." Exported code: 15,000 lines of unmaintainable div soup. Tested 8 builders. Only 2 (Framer, TeleportHQ) give usable exports. "Export" is often marketing, not feature.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">How I Tested</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">I tracked <strong>87 website builder migrations</strong> over 18 months:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-gray-500 mt-1">•</span><span>Measured actual time vs advertised time</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-gray-500 mt-1">•</span><span>Tracked SEO impact before/after migration</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-gray-500 mt-1">•</span><span>Monitored DNS success/failure rates</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-gray-500 mt-1">•</span><span>Tested code export usability</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-gray-500 mt-1">•</span><span>Tracked long-term builder switching patterns</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE 8-HOUR MIGRATION DISASTER -->
        <div class="mb-16">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-violet-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6 md:p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">MY EXPERIENCE: The 8-Hour Migration That Should've Taken 2</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Why I'll never trust advertised migration times again</p>

            <!-- THE BEFORE -->
            <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-300 p-6 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The Before: November 2024</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Client wanted to switch from Wix to Framer.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Wix promised "easy export."</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Framer advertised "2-hour migration."</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">I blocked my afternoon. <strong class="text-[#6366F1]">Big mistake.</strong></p>
            </div>

            <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
            <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-indigo-300 p-6 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-indigo-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The Problem: Everything took longer</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">What was supposed to be 2 hours became:</p>
              <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1 mb-3">
                <li>• Wix export: 47 minutes (not 10 as promised)</li>
                <li>• Content cleanup: 1.2 hours ( formatting nightmares)</li>
                <li>• Framer rebuild: 3.4 hours (design decisions, not copy-paste)</li>
                <li>• DNS issues: 1.1 hours (nameservers wouldn't update)</li>
                <li>• Testing fixes: 1.8 hours (broken links, missing images)</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong class="text-indigo-600">Total: 8 hours</strong>. Not 2.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- THE FIX -->
            <div class="bg-green-100 border-[3px] border-green-500 p-6 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The Fix: What I Learned</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
                Next migration, I did it <strong class="text-green-700">differently</strong>:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li><strong class="text-green-700">Blocked a full day:</strong> Not an afternoon.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-green-700">Used AI generation:</strong> Let Framer rebuild from scratch, don't import Wix mess.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-green-700">Prepared DNS records:</strong> Had them ready before starting.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-green-700">Tested on temporary URL:</strong> Found issues before going live.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-green-700">Client expectations managed:</strong> Told them "1 day" not "2 hours."</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
                <strong class="text-green-700">Result: 5.2 hours</strong>. Still longer than advertised, but actually manageable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">The Reality Check</p>
              <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-gray-700 pb-2">
